.\" Manpage for bitcoin-daemon(1) — bitcoind lifecycle.
.TH BITCOIN-DAEMON 1 "2026-05-21" "bitcoin 1.22.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin\-daemon \- start, stop, monitor, and inspect the local bitcoind

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B start
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B stop
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B monitor
.br
.B bitcoin daemon
.RI [ options ]
.B space
.br
.B bitcoin daemon help
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin daemon
provides a thin lifecycle wrapper over the Bitcoin Core
.BR bitcoind (1)
process: start it, stop it, watch its progress, and report how
much disk the chainstate is consuming. The plugin manages
.BR bitcoind
as a local long-running process; it does not configure systemd
units, nor does it run multiple instances side-by-side.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -d
Enable debug output (shell trace).
.TP
.B -q
Quiet mode (suppress info logging).

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start the local
.BR bitcoind ,
respecting the user's
.I ~/.bitcoin/bitcoin.conf
configuration. Idempotent: if a daemon is already running, prints
its pid and exits 0.
.TP
.B stop
Send the configured shutdown RPC to
.BR bitcoind ;
wait for the process to exit. Idempotent.
.TP
.B monitor
Tail
.BR bitcoind 's
log and emit one progress line per new block (height, time,
sync %).
.TP
.B space
Print disk usage of the chainstate, blocks, indexes, and mempool
directories under
.IR ~/.bitcoin/ .

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B \(>=1
General error. Specific errors emit a
.B warn
or
.B error
line to stderr per CLAUDE.md §10.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/bitcoin.conf
Bitcoin Core configuration the daemon reads at startup.
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/blocks/
.TQ
.I ~/.bitcoin/chainstate/
Block and chainstate directories
.B space
reports on.
.TP
.I ~/.bitcoin/debug.log
The log
.B monitor
tails.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Equivalent to
.BR -d .
.TP
.B SELF_QUIET
Equivalent to
.BR -q .

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR bitcoin-backend (1),
.BR bitcoind (1),
.BR bitcoin-cli (1)

.SH HISTORY
Plugin introduced in bitcoin 1.0.0. Man page added in 1.23.0
(FEAT-041).
